{
  "texts": [
    "Experimental results show that our two-stage method, DIVERSEVAR, achieves the best diversity-quality Pareto frontier.Limitations.",
    "Although our scale-travel refinement technique improves the Pareto frontier, the inference cost is slightly higher than using noise injection (please refer to the supplementary for more details).",
    "We also observe that the most diverse results still suffer from visual artifacts, occurring in approximately 6% of the generated samples.",
    "shows the results for CFG-scheduling and condition-annealing by varying the choice of scheduling functions α(k), β(k), and γ(k).",
    "We limit the maximum value of α(k), β(k) with σ. Cosine and linear schedulers exhibit similar trends and performance on the Pareto front."
  ]
}